OL,3,CWords matter: How to talk about suicide
OL,5,FOne of the main issues with talking
OL,6,Fabout suicide is the words people use
OL,7,Fcommonly to describe a person taking
OL,8,Ftheir own life.
OL,10,FJudd explains: "People are still
OL,11,Ftalking about 'committing suicide'.
OL,12,FIt's not been a crime since 1961 but
OL,13,Fit gives people a sense of judgement.
OL,15,F"Terms like 'you're not going to do
OL,16,Fsomething silly, are you?' These are
OL,17,Fterms that people use without bad
OL,18,Fintent but make others feel like they
OL,19,Fcan't open up to that person.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/7
